<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="robert" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>XSharp.Core</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">XSharp.Core</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">This is the base DLL of the X# Runtime. It contains:</para>
    <list id="3" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#8226;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="List" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="List">Common interfaces, such as IDate, IFloat, ICodeBlock, IMacroCompiler, used by other X# components</li>
      <li styleclass="List">Runtime functions that use standard .Net datatypes such as SLen(), AllTrim(), SLen().</li>
    </list>
    <list id="4" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="List" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="List">The Runtime State (SetDeleted(), SetExact() etc)</li>
      <li styleclass="List">The Workarea information </li>
      <li styleclass="List">The nation resources and collations.</li>
    </list>
    <list id="5" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#8226;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="List" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="List">RDD related functions that do not depend on XBase types as DATE, USUAL and FLOAT.</li>
    </list>
    <list id="4" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="List" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="List">The low level File/IO </li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="List"></para>
    <para styleclass="List">This assembly can be used in all dialects of X#</para>
  </body>
</topic>
